h4. Problem Description

getRowHeight() method not working with android 4.0.4, It shows "has no method'
error.Works fine on IOS simulator.
Steps to reproduce
1.Run following code 

Expected result:
 Alert box should appear with 'rowHeight' value.

Actual result:

Shows 'has no method' error 
h4. Test case
{code}
		var win = Ti.UI.createWindow();
		var tableView = Ti.UI.createTableView({
			rowHeight: 65
		});
		tableView.addEventListener('postlayout', function(){
		alert(tableView.getRowHeight());
		});
		win.add(tableView);
		win.open();
		




{code}
